This paper discusses Service Function Chaining (SFC) which is a technology related to networking and communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses algorithms and optimization problems related to SFC, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper mentions future research directions related to artificial intelligence (AI) and information theory (IT), which could also be relevant categories.
